sparql_query_kg2:
 Based on the provided context and mappings, here is the SPARQL query for Knowledge Graph 2 (Wikidata) to find the highest mountain:

```sparql
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri wdt:P31 wd:Q8502 ;
        wdt:P2044 ?elevation .
} ORDER BY DESC(?elevation) OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1
```

This query uses the mappings from DBpedia to Wikidata to identify the highest mountain by elevation.

