sparql_query_kg2:
 Given the information provided, the task is to convert the SPARQL query for DBpedia to a corresponding query for Wikidata.

Here is the DBpedia query:
```sparql
SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri a <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Swimmer> ;
        <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/birthPlace> <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow>
}
```

Using the mappings provided:
- `<http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Swimmer>` corresponds to `<http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q10843402>`
- `<http://dbpedia.org/ontology/birthPlace>` corresponds to `<http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P19>`
- `<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow>` corresponds to `<http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q649>`

The Wikidata query should look like this:
```sparql
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri wdt:P31 wd:Q10843402 ;
        wdt:P19 wd:Q649 .
}
```

Here is the final, complete SPARQL query for Wikidata:
```sparql
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri wdt:P31 wd:Q10843402 ;
        wdt:P19 wd:Q649 .
}
```

